title: MPCHS cross country team runs in Muscatine
text:
MPCHS cross country team runs in Muscatine Oct 01, 2015 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
MUSCATINE — The Mt. Pleasant cross country teams competed in Muscatine on Tuesday against some of the biggest schools in the area. Along with the Panthers, there were big schools from Cedar Rapids, Davenport and Iowa City that came to compete. The Panther boys scored 234 points for 10th place, and in the girls’ competition, MPCHS finished 11th, with 313 points. 
Leading the boys on Tuesday was Logan Murray who finished in 16:33.9 for ninth place overall. Adam Bodenham clocked in at a 35th place 17:27.4, and Cody Mertens finished 54th, in 18:05.1. 
Other finishers for the Mt. Pleasant boys were Kyle Vanderham (65th, 18:21.4), Dalton Krum (71st, 18:29.5), Ryan Hutchinson (78th, 18:55.5) and Jack Pieper (81st, 19:61.8). Top junior varsity runners were Jonathan Ita (17th, 18:25.3) and Ben Zihlman (39th, 19:11.1). 
On the girls’ side, it was Taylor Murray that led the Panthers with a 36th place 21:39. Delany McDowell finished 53rd, in 22:47. Kelsey Nostestein was 71st, in 24:05, Catherine Prough was 76th, in 26:56, and Ally Davis was 78th, in 27:04. 
Leading junior varsity runners on the girls’ side were Megan Hoenig, who finished 102nd, in 27:08, and Laurie Amos, who was 125th, in 28:44. 
“We knew this was going to be a hard meet for us,” said girls’ coach Jean Caboth. “The course was hilly and challenged our runners.” 
The Panthers will be back in action on Tuesday, Oct. 6 at 4:30 p.m. for a meet in Centerville. Among the competitors in Centerville will be conference rivals Ft. Madison and Keokuk.
